Former Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas has passed away, and President Obama has sent his condolences to the people of Lithuania on behalf of the American people. President Brazauskas played a significant role in the restoration of Lithuania's independence and had a strong commitment to democracy. He also strengthened Lithuania's security relationships with the NATO alliance and guided its integration into the European Union. The relationship between the United States and Lithuania grew under President Brazauskas' leadership, based on shared interests and values. The American people mourn the loss of a great man who dedicated his life to his country, its freedom, and its security.